callgraph
Class GraphConverter

java.lang.Object
  callgraph.GraphConverter
public class GraphConverter
extends java.lang.Object

Converts graphs to different hierarchy levels (method, class or package). And calculates annotations.

Author:
Christopher Oßner TODO should be moved to bl.tools as java1.6 can be used there, we really would benefit from generics. No need to have this class here (it is not used during the trace). Maybe different converters for the different hirarchy levels...

Calculates annotations for the adjacency list passed as first argument.

Parameters:
al - graph to calculate annotations for
toMeth - map of package -> {}, needed for called-methods
toClass - map of package -> {}, needed for called-classes
fromMeth - map of method -> {}, needed for calling-methods
fromClass - map of class -> {}, needed for calling-classes
Returns:
al, with annotations

private AdjacenceList calculateClassAnnotations(AdjacenceList al,
                                                java.util.HashMap toMeth,
                                                java.util.HashMap fromMeth,
                                                java.util.HashSet packnames)
Calculates annotations for the adjacency list passed as first argument.

Parameters:
al -
toMeth - toMeth map of package -> {}, needed for called-methods
fromMeth - map of method -> {}, needed for calling-methods
packnames - packages to considered, used to look up if we deal with a 'ForeignPackage' method (not very clean implementation - caused by bad design of Signature)
Returns:
al with annotations
